text: I know this is a silly pet peeve, but don't call your deck a tribal deck if it's just goodstuff and three fucking dragons or whatever. There's nothing wrong with just jamming a ton of good cards into a deck. It's not my idea of an interesting build, but whatever, you be boring you. But don't pretend your Unesh deck built entirely around Deadeye Navigator combos to get to Labman is a "sphinx tribal deck" when the only other sphinx is Consecrated. Own that shit and admit you're boring and lame.

MTG Story:
Samut and Djeru go back into the city to help Hazoret with a band of other warriors.
Neheb shows up! Apparently he's a legend among the city.
Gatewatch shows up and Neheb is dead :(
Hazoret is injured and fighting the Scorpion God, even cutting her arm off after being stung.
Djeru, Samut and their band push the Scorpion God back until it becomes impaled by an obelisk after a Jackal knocks it back with Rhonas' staff.
Hazoret finishes off the God, incinerating it inside out.
Samut sparks and planeswalks to Theros.

Have they stated before whether where a spark takes a planeswalker is random or if there's something else behind it? Samut bouncing to a plane with gods seems like there's some cosmic logic at work. Nissa went to one with a lot of elves, Chandra a fire-heavy plane, etc.
I don't think any particulars have really been explored, but I saw someone point out that exact thing earlier today. Gideon to Bant, Jace to Ravnica, Liliana to Innistrad.
